<subSubSection id="093CDE3B1E77B388603BBF66F060D53B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="ABD3BD9656B5152A11F9DF7711742B7B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF3B060CEB272FCED8EA83BB23EF93EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
A species of the western Chaco in northern Argentina, western Paraguay and southern Bolivia. It is a lowland species of roadsides and disturbed bushy habitats, not found above 600 m. It is particularly common around the city of Santa Cruz in Bolivia. We have not traced the record from Brazil (Austin and 
<normalizedToken id="562800E435ADE00F17C3EFA79776EBD2" originalValue="Huáman">Huaman</normalizedToken>
1996), which seems improbable.
</paragraph>
